&lt;p&gt;Translation [[Ogihara 2009]]: 358:&lt;br&gt;
a1 /// there is a monk. If a woman ... from below ///&lt;br&gt;
a2 /// if here is unordained, being in the same behaviour ///&lt;br&gt;
a3 /// if he is covered in the door of the cell or of the dwelling-place ///&lt;br&gt;
a4 /// if he does not abandon (this insight), he brings about Pāt. || ... ///&lt;br&gt;
a5 /// the monk commits Pāt.-sin. ///&lt;br&gt;
b1 /// they give the ritual formula. Kept away form the community ///&lt;br&gt;
b2 /// (if a monk) finds pleasure in service (to him) or with him ///&lt;br&gt;
b3 /// the intention of the attachment to the insight ... ///&lt;br&gt;
b4 /// Pāt named [Utkṣiptānuvṛtti] ends. 6 || But a novice ///&lt;br&gt;
b5 /// they give the ritual formula to him. In this way, ... him ///
&lt;/p&gt;</item>
